<plot>The Game had 3 Stars and 20 contestants who played for a weekday broadcast and along with "A Name Dropper"-A Person who in some way had a connection to 1 of the 3 celebrities. Examples were: A Maid, 1st Grade Teacher or Mechanic. The Stars told stories about how they related to the "Name Dropper." The Contestants voted for the star what story they believed. If they were correct they each collect $10 (possibly $200). "The Name Dropper" collected $10 for each wrong vote. In Addition, Each Game had 2 Contestants got a chance to explain why they chose as they did and then played for a bonus prize. The Contestant with the greatest number of correct answers on a weekday's worth wins a $1000 Bonus.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?388977</url></doc>
